    <refsection id="Description_TKSCALE">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This source block generates a piecewise constant signal the value of which can be set interactively using a widget in the course of the simulation. The output value is the value set by the slider (an integer between Min value and Max value) divided by the Normalization factor. Increasing proportionally all three block parameters does not change the output range, but it does increase precision.
        </para>
        <para>
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection id="Dialogbox_TKSCALE">
        <title>Dialog box</title>
        <para>
            <inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../../../gui/sources_pal/en_US/TKSCALE_gui.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>
                </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject>
        </para>
        <para>

        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold">Min value</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para> An integer specifying the min value in the range of the scale.</para>
                <para> Properties : Type 'vec' of size 1. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold">Max value</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para> An integer specifying the max value in the range of the scale.</para>
                <para> Properties : Type 'vec' of size 1. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <emphasis role="bold">Normalization</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para> The output of the block is the integer value specified by the slider (an integer between Min value and the Max value) divided by this Normalization factor.</para>
                <para> Properties : Type 'vec' of size 1.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </refsection>
